in Europe today.\", \"from\": 2091, \"to\": 2161, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Ring  The Ring is Euronews' weekly political showdown, where Europe's toughest debates meet their boldest voices.\", \"from\": 2163, \"to\": 2280, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In each episode, two political heavyweights from across the EU face off to propose a diversity of opinions and spark conversations around the most important issues of EU affairs and the wider European political life.\", \"from\": 2283, \"to\": 2499, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2343, \"end\": 2345, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 2.5268097070723685e-13, \"text\": \"EU\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\"}, {\"begin\": 2450, \"end\": 2452, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 2.5268097070723685e-13, \"text\": \"EU\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No Comment  No agenda, no argument, no bias, No Comment.\", \"from\": 2501, \"to\": 2557, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Get the story without commentary.\", \"from\": 2558, \"to\": 2591, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"My Wildest Prediction  Dare to imagine the future with business and tech visionaries  The Big Question  Deep dive conversations with business leaders  Euronews Tech Talks  Euronews Tech Talks goes beyond discussions to explore the impact of new technologies on our lives.\", \"from\": 2593, \"to\": 2864, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With explanations, engaging Q&As, and lively conversations, the podcast provides valuable insights into the intersection of technology and society.\", \"from\": 2865, \"to\": 3012, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Food Detectives  Europe's best food experts are joining forces to crack down on fraud.\", \"from\": 3014, \"to\": 3104, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Euronews is following them in this special series: The Food Detectives  Water Matters  Europe's water is under increasing pressure.\", \"from\": 3105, \"to\": 3236, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3160, \"end\": 3175, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Food_Detectives\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Food Detectives\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Food_Detectives\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Food_Detectives\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pollution, droughts, floods are taking their toll on our drinking water, lakes, rivers and coastlines.\", \"from\": 3237, \"to\": 3339, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Join us on a journey around Europe to see why protecting ecosystems matters, how our wastewater can be better managed, and to discover some of the best water solutions.\", \"from\": 3340, \"to\": 3508, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Video reports, an animated explainer series and live debate - find out why Water Matters, from Euronews.\", \"from\": 3511, \"to\": 3615, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3606, \"end\": 3614, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Euronews\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Euronews\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Euronews\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Euronews\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Climate Now  We give you the latest climate facts from the world's leading source, analyse the trends and explain how our planet is changing.\", \"from\": 3617, \"to\": 3758, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We meet the experts on the front line of climate change who explore new strategies to mitigate and adapt.\", \"from\": 3759, \"to\": 3864, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"French DJ, LGBTQ+ icon and feminist activist Barbara Butch has announced that she has filed a complaint, as she has been the subject of \\\"a campaign of cyber harassment and defamation\\\" of \\\"unprecedented\\\" violence, following her appearance at theParis Olympic Games opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 3866, \"to\": 4147, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3866, \"end\": 3872, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9991899349912541, \"rank\": 0.0005860724746291363, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 3911, \"end\": 3924, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"score\": 0.9999897744159937, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Barbara Butch\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If at first I decided not to speak out to let the haters calm down, the messages I am receiving are more and more extreme,\\\" she wrote on her Instagram account.\", \"from\": 4149, \"to\": 4309, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4291, \"end\": 4300, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.7756375154690645e-33, \"text\": \"Instagram\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"All this for having had the chance to represent the diversity of my country through art and music, alongside other artists and performers I admire.\\\"\", \"from\": 4310, \"to\": 4459, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Audrey Msellati, Butch's lawyer, said that her client was facing threats of \\\"death, torture and rape\\\", as well as \\\"numerous anti-Semitic, homophobic, sexist and fatphobic insults\\\".\", \"from\": 4461, \"to\": 4641, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4461, \"end\": 4467, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Audrey_Roberts\", \"score\": 0.9999999999772626, \"rank\": 2.2550648524010793e-11, \"text\": \"Audrey\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Audrey_Roberts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Audrey_Roberts\"}, {\"begin\": 4585, \"end\": 4597, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antisemitism\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4030893667461123e-15, \"text\": \"anti-Semitic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antisemitism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antisemitism\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Butch \\\"is filing a complaint today for these acts, whether committed by nationals or foreigners, and intends to prosecute anyone who, in the future, seeks to intimidate her\\\", added Msellati.\", \"from\": 4643, \"to\": 4833, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Butch, who promotes \\\"love and inclusivity\\\", insists that she is \\\"not afraid of those who hide behind a screen, or a pseudonym, to spew their hatred and frustrations.\\\"\", \"from\": 4835, \"to\": 5001, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"French association SOS homophobie issued the following statement in the wake of Butch's complaint: \\\"SOS homophobie gives total support to Barbara Butch in the face of waves of cyber harassment she has suffered since the opening ceremony: threats of death, torture, rape, antisemitic, homophobic, sexist and fatphobic insults.\", \"from\": 5003, \"to\": 5328, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5003, \"end\": 5009, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9991899349912541, \"rank\": 0.0005860724746291363, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 5022, \"end\": 5036, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/SOS_Homophobie\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"SOS homophobie\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/SOS_Homophobie\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/SOS_Homophobie\"}, {\"begin\": 5141, \"end\": 5154, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"score\": 0.9999897744159937, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Barbara Butch\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hatred will not pass.\\\"\", \"from\": 5329, \"to\": 5351, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Butch performed at the opening ceremony on Friday 26 July, alongside\\u00a0dancers and drag artists like Nicky Doll and Paloma, in a tableau entitled \\\"Festivit\\u00e9\\\".\", \"from\": 5353, \"to\": 5509, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5467, \"end\": 5473, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paloma_Picasso\", \"score\": 0.999999545057666, \"rank\": 4.546030958019067e-07, \"text\": \"Paloma\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paloma_Picasso\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paloma_Picasso\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to its detractors, this sequence is a parody of Leonardo da Vinci's \\\"The Last Supper\\\", and it has caused quite the ruckus.\", \"from\": 5511, \"to\": 5643, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5569, \"end\": 5586, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.86997061860117e-22, \"text\": \"Leonardo da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French Bishops' Conference (CEF) deplored \\\"scenes of derision and mockery of Christianity\\\" - a sentiment echoed by Russian Foreign Ministry spokesperson Maria Zakharova.\", \"from\": 5645, \"to\": 5818, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5677, \"end\": 5680, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Expeditionary_Force\", \"score\": 0.9994039989522889, \"rank\": 0.0005963564769379811, \"text\": \"CEF\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Expeditionary_Force\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Expeditionary_Force\"}, {\"begin\": 5726, \"end\": 5738, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999990248880046, \"rank\": 9.737873191006328e-07, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 5764, \"end\": 5788, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ministry_of_Foreign_Affairs_(Russia)\", \"score\": 0.999999999875854, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Russian Foreign Ministry\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ministry_of_Foreign_Affairs_(Russia)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ministry_of_Foreign_Affairs_(Russia)\"}, {\"begin\": 5802, \"end\": 5817, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maria_Zakharova\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Maria Zakharova\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maria_Zakharova\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maria_Zakharova\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Elsewhere, the Anglican Communion in Egypt expressed its \\\"deep regret\\\", saying the ceremony could cause the IOC (International Olympic Committee) to \\\"lose its distinctive sporting identity and its humanitarian message.\\\"\", \"from\": 5819, \"to\": 6038, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5834, \"end\": 5852, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anglican_Communion\", \"score\": 0.9980461047614989, \"rank\": 0.0019577204189475564, \"text\": \"Anglican Communion\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anglican_Communion\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anglican_Communion\"}, {\"begin\": 5856, \"end\": 5861, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\", \"score\": 0.9999999828032743, \"rank\": 1.0349315965592908e-08, \"text\": \"Egypt\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\"}, {\"begin\": 5927, \"end\": 5930, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.085881023921856e-21, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 5932, \"end\": 5963, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then there is Andrew Tate, the controversial media personality awaiting trial on charges of human trafficking, rape and forming a criminal gang to sexually exploit women...\", \"from\": 6040, \"to\": 6212, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6061, \"end\": 6065, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tate\", \"score\": 0.9997170215751676, \"rank\": 0.0002829473240008194, \"text\": \"Tate\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tate\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tate\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He and his brother Tristan Tate were also among the critics of this segment of the opening ceremony, andstood in front of a churchnear the French Embassy in Bucharest to protest.\", \"from\": 6213, \"to\": 6391, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6232, \"end\": 6239, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tristan\", \"score\": 0.9999999919709808, \"rank\": 8.028789000715863e-09, \"text\": \"Tristan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tristan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tristan\"}, {\"begin\": 6240, \"end\": 6244, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tate\", \"score\": 0.9997170215751676, \"rank\": 0.0002829473240008194, \"text\": \"Tate\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tate\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tate\"}, {\"begin\": 6370, \"end\": 6379, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bucharest\", \"score\": 0.9999999999868123, \"rank\": 1.3239499485746804e-11, \"text\": \"Bucharest\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bucharest\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bucharest\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Elon Musk also voiced his opinion, writing on X: \\\"Unless there is more bravery to stand up for what is fair and right, Christianity will perish,\\\" while Donald Trump also could not resist chipping in, describing the opening ceremony, and in particular the drag-queen sequence, as a \\\"disgrace\\\".\", \"from\": 6393, \"to\": 6685, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6393, \"end\": 6402, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elon_Musk\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Elon Musk\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elon_Musk\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elon_Musk\"}, {\"begin\": 6512, \"end\": 6524, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999990248880046, \"rank\": 9.737873191006328e-07, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 6545, \"end\": 6557, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.9999998252337872, \"rank\": 1.7475886385102696e-07, \"text\": \"Donald Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am very open-minded, but I thought what they did was a disgrace,\\\" said the former US president in an interview with Fox News.\", \"from\": 6687, \"to\": 6815, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6772, \"end\": 6774, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9977890766749423, \"rank\": 0.0022148019405816323, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 6806, \"end\": 6814, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.783935572183626e-31, \"text\": \"Fox News\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The ceremony's artistic director,Thomas Jolly, assured that the sequence was \\\"a great pagan festival linked to the gods of Olympus.\\\"\", \"from\": 6817, \"to\": 6949, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6850, \"end\": 6856, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\", \"score\": 0.9999926918302319, \"rank\": 7.3081756036350455e-06, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\"}, {\"begin\": 6940, \"end\": 6947, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mount_Olympus\", \"score\": 0.9774302507714362, \"rank\": 0.023090905155981726, \"text\": \"Olympus\", \"types\": [\"Q8502\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mount_Olympus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mount_Olympus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We wanted to talk about diversity.\", \"from\": 6951, \"to\": 6986, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Diversity means being together.\", \"from\": 6987, \"to\": 7018, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We wanted to include everybody.\", \"from\": 7019, \"to\": 7050, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In France, we have artistic freedom.\", \"from\": 7051, \"to\": 7087, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7054, \"end\": 7060, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9996245202717046, \"rank\": 0.0003561075135622898, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We are lucky in France to live in a free country,\\\" said Jolly, regarding the negative reactions to the show.\", \"from\": 7088, \"to\": 7196, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7104, \"end\": 7110, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9996245202717046, \"rank\": 0.0003561075135622898, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However,\\u00a0a spokesperson for Paris 2024 issued an apology: \\\"Clearly there was never an intention to show disrespect to any religious group.\", \"from\": 7198, \"to\": 7336, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7226, \"end\": 7236, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5184103618025507e-18, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[The opening ceremony] tried to celebrate community tolerance,\\\"\\u00a0Anne Descamps told the press.\", \"from\": 7337, \"to\": 7430, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7406, \"end\": 7414, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Descamps\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We believe this ambition was achieved.\", \"from\": 7431, \"to\": 7470, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If people have taken any offence we are really sorry.\\\"\", \"from\": 7471, \"to\": 7525, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Browse today's tags\", \"from\": 7531, \"to\": 7550, \"entities\": []}]}"